header.gameNote: CANCUN CHALLENGE AT PLAYA DEL CARMEN MEXICO

article.headline: North Florida 59, Morgan St. 52
article.story: PLAYA DEL CARMEN, Mexico -- Andy Diaz, Matt Sauey and Parker Smith scored 11 points apiece as North Florida defeated Morgan State 59-52 on Wednesday. The Ospreys (3-3) used a smothering defense -- holding the Bears to 32.3 percent shooting (20 of 62) -- to win the championship game of the Cancun Challenge -- Mayan Division bracket. Morgan State (2-3) shot only 1 of 11 from 3-point range. North Florida was 22 of 56 (39.3 percent) from the floor, but made 7 of 16 3-pointers. Morgan State used a 16-4 run spanning the end of the first half and beginning of the second to lead 31-29. Jimmy Williams' layup and a Smith 3-pointer pushed the Ospreys ahead for good. DeWayne Jackson scored 12 points and Kevin Thompson had 10 points and 10 rebounds for the Bears, who outrebounded North Florida 44-31. Jerron Granberry, who had eight points and seven rebounds for North Florida, was named Tournament MVP.
